#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:1
msgid "For Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:3
msgid ""
"_Are user-facing docs and compatibility artifacts correct, current, and well-"
"written?_"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:5
msgid ""
"This is the index of the **documentation** guidelines. Each subsection is "
"its own page, and each entry below links a stable `short-name` to its "
"guideline, with a one-line gist so a reader (or a review tool) can grasp the "
"guideline before opening it."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:10
msgid "Index"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:12
msgid "**[General Style](general-style.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:13
msgid ""
"[`semantic-line-breaks`](general-style.md#semantic-line-breaks): Break prose "
"at sentence/clause boundaries, one idea per line."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:14
msgid ""
"[`readme-as-crate-doc`](general-style.md#readme-as-crate-doc): For a "
"published crate, make `README.md` the crate-level doc (`#![doc = include_str!"
"(\"../README.md\")]`) so crates.io and docs.rs stay in sync."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:16
msgid "**[Path-Specific](path-specific/)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:17
msgid "[`kernel/`](path-specific/kernel.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/index.md:18
msgid ""
"[`linux-compat-docs`](path-specific/kernel.md#linux-compat-docs): When a "
"user-visible API (syscall or kernel parameter) changes, update the Linux "
"Compatibility docs (Syscall Flag Coverage + `.scml`, or Kernel Parameters)."
msgstr ""
